# Project Structure

## Directory Organization

```
wdv/
├── *.html                 # Main application pages
├── js/                    # JavaScript modules
│   ├── common.js          # Shared utilities (pure functions)
│   ├── live_updates.js    # API client + offline sync
│   └── [module].js        # Feature-specific modules
├── api/
│   ├── index.php          # RESTful API router
│   ├── db.php             # Database + auth layer
│   └── sql/               # Database migrations
├── css/
│   ├── tailwind-compiled.css  # Compiled Tailwind (generated)
│   └── score-colors.css       # Archery ring colors (allowed exception)
├── tests/
│   ├── api/               # API tests
│   ├── components/        # Component tests (style-guide.html)
│   └── *.spec.js          # Playwright tests
└── docs/                  # Documentation
    ├── core/              # Essential reference docs
    ├── guides/            # How-to guides
    ├── features/          # Feature documentation
    └── implementation/    # Implementation details
```

## File Naming Conventions

### HTML Files
- Lowercase with underscores: `ranking_round_300.html`, `solo_card.html`
- Descriptive names indicating purpose

### JavaScript Files
- Lowercase with underscores: `archer_module.js`, `live_updates.js`
- Module pattern when appropriate (e.g., `ArcherModule` object)

### SQL Files
- Migrations: `migration_[description].sql`
- Schema: `schema.mysql.sql`
- Scripts: `backfill_[description].sql`

### Documentation
- Root docs: `[NUMBER-]SCREAMING_CASE.md` (e.g., `01-SESSION_QUICK_START.md`)
- Docs folder: `UPPERCASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES.md`

## Module Integration

**Standardized Components:**
- `js/archer_selector.js` - Standardized archer selection
- `js/score_keypad.js` - Touch-optimized score input
- `js/scorecard_view.js` - Scorecard rendering utilities

**When creating new features:**
1. Check if standardized components exist
2. Reuse existing patterns from Ranking Round 300 (most integrated)
3. Follow mobile-first principles
4. Use Tailwind exclusively

